d43 1
a43 1
function generates a string, that, when used as a pathname, refers to
d63 6
a68 4
Upon successful completion, a non-null pointer is returned.
Otherwise, a null pointer is returned and the global variable
.Va errno
is set to indicate the error.
a77 7
.Sh BUGS
By default the
.Fn ctermid
function writes all information to an internal static object.
Subsequent calls to
.Fn ctermid
will modify the same object.
